f_n = \dfrac{e^{nx}}{e^{nx}+e^{-nx}}
\mathbb{R}
f_n = 1/2
x = 0
f_n = \dfrac{e^{2nx}}{e^{2nx}+1}
x \neq 0
f = \begin{cases} 1/2 & \text{ if } x= 0\\  1 & \text{ if } x > 0 \\  1 & \text{ if } x < 0  \end{cases}
\lim_{n \to \infty}|f - f_n| = 0
\,x<0\iff -x>0\,
f_n(x)=\frac{e^{2nx}}{1+e^{2nx}}=\frac1{1+e^{-2nx}}\xrightarrow[n\to\infty]{}0
f(x)=\begin{cases}0&,\;\;\;x<0\\{}\\\frac12&,\;\;\;x=0\\{}\\{}\\1&,\;\;\;x>0\end{cases}
e^{nx}
f_n=\frac{1}{1+e^{-2nx}}
